info.name: GFS API
info.description:
The family of API'S Detailed in this Document are offered to help retailers drive down cart abandonment while increasing transparency and consumer options through one integration.

The API enpoint is only reachable by HTTPS and any HTTP request will be rejected, we accept json payloads as a standard. Minimum TLS version is TLS1.2 any request using older versions will be rejected.

**Test/Staging Enviroment**
Note: Your Client ID and secret will be provided your welcome email from the registration system.

Item | Value 
--- | --- 
API URL | https://sandbox.gfsdeliver.com/ (This is only available for GFS Duties and taxes currently)
Portal access | url will go here

**Production Enviroment**
Note: Your Client ID and secret will be provided your welcome email from the registration system.

Item | Value 
--- | --- 
API URL | https://connect2.gfsdeliver.com/
Portal access | https://checkout.justshoutgfs.com


# Status Codes
Status Codes vary depending on the endpoint that is being called however generally the below status will be returned.

Response Code | Description
--- | --- 
200 | OK
201 | Created
204 | The id exists and is valid
400 | The data supplied was invalid
401 | Unauthorized
403 | Authorization error
404 | Bad Request
500 | Internal server error

item.name: Calculate duty and tax for an order

header.description: This is the access_token that you generated from the authorization request

request.description:
#### Request This call is to obtain any taxes or Duty required for an order based on the information provided. #### Field Parameters Below is a list of all the supported field names at item/order level. Field Name | Required | Example value --- | --- | --- **OrderID** | **Mandatory** | **my unique order** **deliveryDate** | **Mandatory** | **2020-01-12** **currencyCode** | **Mandatory** | **GBP** to.address | Optional | GFS, Piries Place to.city | Optional | Horsham to.region | Optional | West Sussex **to.postCode** | **Mandatory** | **RH12 1EH** **to.countryCode** | **Mandatory** | **GB** to.address | Optional | GFS, to.city | Optional | Woodbridge to.region | Optional | New Jersey **to.postCode** | **Mandatory** | **07001** **to.countryCode** | **Mandatory** | **US** **items[X].itemId** | **Mandatory** | **Messenger Bag** **items[X].productCode** | **Mandatory** | **t123** **items[X].hsCode** | **Mandatory** | **6403519030** **items[X].quantity** | **Mandatory** | **1** **items[X].value** | **Mandatory** | **12.95** items[X].manufactured.country | Optional | GB items[X].sku | Optional | test123 **to.postcode is only mandatory where applicable**
**If no to.postcode then address and region must be provide.** #### Response WIthin the response there is information at different levels depending on your requirement this is broken down in the below levels Type | Description --- | --- Summary | This is a summary of the order and provides the highest level of detail on taxes. details | This provides details on the different tax types applicable for this order item | This details a summary of the item details item details | This returns the details for each item tax type see below for the full list of Response parameters Name | Type | Notes --- | --- | --- orderId | string | This is the orderId you provided on the request currencyCode | string | This will always return the same value as you passed in the request totalValue | number | This is the total value of the order excluding tax totalTaxable | number | The total taxable value (future release will allow you to pass an taxOverride value on items) totalTax | number | The total tax for all items in this transaction totalTaxCalculated | number | The total amount of tax that GFS calculated for the transaction. If you used a *taxOverride* of type *taxAmount* for any items in this transaction, this value will represent the amount that GFS calculated for this transaction without applying the override. The field totalTax will be the total amount of tax after all overrides are applied. You can compare the *totalTax* and *totalTaxCalculated* fields to check for any discrepancies between an external tax calculation provider and the calculation performed by GFS taxCalculatedDate | string | The date the tax was calculated, in format YYYY-MM-DD items|array|This is the complete list of item detail which is provided with tax data against it. ###### items array each item line will return the below Name | Type | Notes --- | --- | --- itemId | string | A unique identifier for this instance of order item, provided in the request. productCode | string | The productCode provided in the request. sku | string | The sku provided in the request. hsCode | string | the HS code provided in the request quantity | number | Quantity of the item provided in the request value | number | the value of the item tax | number | The total tax for this item of the transaction TaxCalculated | number | the total tax calculated for this item taxableAmount | number | The portion of the item amount of this transaction that was taxable. details | array | this provdes details on the different tax types ###### Details array For the details of will be returned the below this is provided at the overall level and at a item level Name | Type | Notes --- | --- | --- country | string | The two-character ISO 3166 code of the country for this transaction. region | string | The two-or-three character ISO region code of the region for this transaction. juristype | enum | The type of the jurisdiction in which this tax detail applies.
*Country*
*State*
*City*
*special* juriscode | string | The code of the jurisdiction to which this tax detail applies. jurisname | string |The name of the jurisdiction to which this tax detail applies. rate | number | The rate at which this tax detail was calculated. ratetypecode | string |Indicates the code of the rate type that was used to calculate this tax detail. taxtype | string | the type of tax that was calculated. Depends on the company's nexus settings as well as the jurisdiction's tax laws. taxname | string | The name of the tax against which this tax amount was calculated. tax | number | The amount of tax for this tax detail. taxcalculated | number | The amount of tax that GFS calculated. If an override for tax amount is used, there may be a difference between the tax field which applies your override, and the this amount that is calculated without override. taxsubtype | string | The unique human readable Id of this tax sub-type. taxoverride | number | The amount of tax override that was specified for this tax item. taxableunits | number | Number of units in this item that were calculated to be taxable according to this rate detail.

exec: pm.test("Response time is less than 500ms", function() {

header.description: This is the access_token that you generated from the authorization request
Accept header with version required to use v2

request.description:
#### Request
This is the Inital call made to generate the session for each of the customer requests, a new session must be created for each order that you wish to obtain delivery options for.

#### Field Parameters
Below is a list of all the supported field names at item/order level.

Field Name | Required | Example value
--- | --- | ---
**options.startDate** | **Mandatory** | **2021-01-14**
**options.endDate** | **Mandatory** | **2021-03-23**
**options.currency** | **Mandatory** | **GBP**
options.droppoints.max | Optional | 20
options.droppoints.radius | Optional | 50000
options.stores.max | Optional | 30
options.stores.radius | Optional | 30000
order.delivery.origin.street | Optional | GFS,  Piries Place
order.delivery.origin.city | Optional | Horsham
order.delivery.origin.state | Optional | West Sussex
**order.delivery.origin.zip** | **Mandatory** | **RH12 1EH**
**order.delivery.origin.country** | **Mandatory** | **GB**
order.delivery.destination.street | Optional | GFS,  Unit 3 Taurus Park
order.delivery.destination.city | Optional | Warrington
order.delivery.destination.state | Optional | Cheshire
**order.delivery.destination.zip** | **Mandatory** | **WA5 7ZT**
**order.delivery.destination.country** | **Mandatory** | **GB**
order.packs | Optional | 15
order.taxes.type | Optional | sales / landedcost
order.taxes.amount | Optional | 5
**order.price** | **Mandatory** | **165.32**
order.additionalData[x].name | Optional | Additionalvaluename123
order.additionalData[x].value | Optional | Mandatory for every order.additionalData[0].name provided
order.items[X].countryOfManufacture | Optional | EU
**order.items[X].description** | **Mandatory** | **Item description free text**
**order.items[X].price** | **Mandatory** | **11.25**
order.items[X].dimensions.unit | Optional | cm
order.items[X].dimensions.length | Optional | 15
order.items[X].dimensions.height | Optional | 56
order.items[X].dimensions.width | Optional | 24
order.items[X].weight.unit | Optional | g
order.items[X].weight.value | Optional | 764
**order.items[X].productCode** | **Mandatory** | **ProdCode123**
order.items[X].sku | Optional | SKU-123
**order.items[X].quantity** | **Mandatory** | **15**
order.items[X].taxes.type | Optional | sales / landedcost
order.items[X].taxes.amount | Optional | 5
order.items[X].additionalData[x].name | Optional | Additionalitemvaluename123
order.items[X].additionalData[x].value | Optional | Mandatory for every order.items[X].additionalData[0].name provided
order.items[X].hazardous[X] | Optional | Hazard-C3


#### Response
###### **No body is returned **

A response header **location** is returned and this is the  *_session_* which is required to GET and DEL the session details at a later stage

# Day Definite Availability
This method returns all the available day definite dates for the session.
The results will be the entire period that was sent in the **POST**.

The *select URi* that is returned in the response can be used as the URi which will return the specific day requested to do this you can take the *base* and combine the *select* which will give you the specific day.

request.description:

List all options available for a set period 2. list standard delivery options 3. list day definite options 4. list droppoints only 5. list store only a combination of these can be used and seen in the examples.
